==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discouragement
<hw>Dis*cour"age*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>descouragement</ets>, F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧couragement</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of discouraging, or the state of being
discouraged; depression or weakening of confidence; dejection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which discourages; that which deters, or tends
to deter, from an undertaking, or from the prosecution of anything; a
determent; <as>as, the revolution was commenced under every possible
<ex>discouragement</ex></as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Discouragements</xex>
from vice.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discourager</ent>⟦br⟧
